<HEAD>Tornado Slams Florida; Thunderstorms in the Rockies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Scattered thunderstorms continued over the Southeast today, part
of a storm system that spawned a tornado that roared through a
Florida town and cut a mile-long swathe of destruction.
   The twister Sunday in South Fort Myers damaged the roofs of 10
businesses and 29 boats from a marine sales business. It slammed
one boat into an office building, and also damaged 36 mobile homes
and seven condomiums.
   Thunderstorms erupted Sunday evening across the Rockies. High
winds blew down large trees at Helena, Mont., and winds gusted up
to 58 mph at Elko, Nev.
   Scattered thunderstorms doused Kentucky, the Tennessee and lower
Mississippi valleys, and parts of Texas.
   Heavy rainfall during the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included 1.5 inches at Tampa, Fla., .98 inches at Centreville,
Ala., .69 inches at Farmington, N.M., and half an inch at
Knoxville, Tenn.
   Fog hung today over the Ohio Valley, the Great Lakes and the
northern and Middle Atlantic Coast.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms during the
afternoon and evening across the central Rockies, the Plains, Texas
and much of the Southeast and Gulf region.
   Highs were to be in the 70s across the central and northern
Pacific Coast; in the 90s across much of Nevada and Utah, the
central Rockies to the northern Plains, in central and southern
Texas, in Florida, and from the Carolinas to Long Island; from 100
to 110 degrees across the Desert Southwest; and in the 80s
elsewhere.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 44 degrees at
Yellowstone, Wyo., to 98 degrees at Blythe, Calif.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 72 cloudy; Boston 68 fair; Buffalo 69 partly
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 72 fair; Cincinnati 70 foggy; Cleveland 71
foggy; Detroit 72 foggy; Miami 82 partly cloudy; New York 73 fair;
Philadelphia 74 hazy; Pittsburgh 73 foggy; Portland, Maine 58 fair;
Washington 79 hazy.
   _Central: Bismarck 66 partly cloudy; Chicago 72 fair;
Dallas-Fort Worth 68 fair; Denver 70 windy; Des Moines 69 foggy;
Indianapolis 71 foggy; Kansas City 69 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 69
fair; Nashville 73 fair; New Orleans 70 fair; St. Louis 73 foggy.
   _West: Albuquerque 65 cloudy; Anchorage 53 rain; Las Vegas 92
fair; Los Angeles 64 cloudy; Phoenix 94 fair; Salt Lake City 74
fair; San Diego 68 fair; San Francisco 53 fair; Seattle 62 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 72 fair; Toronto 68 hazy.
