<FIRST>r i PM-Britain-Beans     07-24 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Britain-Beans,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>HP Says Glass Slivers Deliberately Placed in Beans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   HP Foods Ltd. said today that slivers of glass
were deliberately placed in cans of baked beans while they were
being processed last month, and police are investigating.
   Glass has been found in six cans of HP Beans, all bought from
the same supermarket in Barnsley, central England.
   HP said in a statement that the cans were part of a batch of
200,000 canned on June 21 at its factory in North Walsham in
eastern England and sent to northern England. The time of the
canning is known to within five minutes, it said.
   ``It is generally agreed that it could not have happened during
the normal process of production and therefore we must assume it
(the glass) was deliberately placed,'' said a company spokesman,
requesting anonymity.
   HP said most of the cans in the batch had been located and were
on their way back to the company.
