<FIRST>r a PM-VictimJailed     07-24 0366</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Victim Jailed,0378</SECOND>
<HEAD>Judge Sends Rape Victim to Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who was jailed for six days
for refusing to testify against a man charged with raping her says
she's angrier at the legal system than at her alleged attacker.
   The 22-year-old woman _ who said she ignored court summonses
because she didn't want to relive the assault _ said her arrest at
first seemed like a second kidnapping and she was frightened when
her lawyer couldn't seem to get her freed.
   ``I thought I was never getting out,'' the woman told the Miami
Herald in an interview from California that was published over the
weekend.
   ``It was like, `I can't believe this is happening to me,''' she
said. ``... I'm just very angry, more at the system than at my
attacker.''
   The woman was jailed June 15 after Broward County Circuit Judge
Mark Speiser ordered her arrested and brought to court so he could
ask her if she was willing to testify against Steven L. Lord, 26,
an unemployed mechanic.
   Lord is charged with armed sexual battery and armed kidnapping
in an assault on the woman, who was kidnapped from a restaurant
parking lot and assaulted Nov. 6.
   When the woman finally was brought into court June 20, the judge
scolded her.
   ``It disturbs me that, since you are the victim of this crime,
that you have totally ignored your obligation to appear in court
and appear for depositions,'' Speiser said.
   She was freed that day after agreeing to testify at the trial,
which is scheduled to begin Aug. 21.
   The judge said he didn't intend that the woman be jailed.
Deputies who arrested her were supposed to bring her straight to
court, he said.
   ``I had no idea when they picked her up,'' Speiser told the
Herald last week. ``Why they didn't bring her to me, I don't know.''
   But those weren't the orders jailers got from the judge, said
Maj. Willie Roberts, a jail director. He read from a computer
print-out of directions to jailers: ``Subject is to be remanded
into custody of Broward County Jail until she can be brought before
Judge Speiser _ no bond.''
</TEXT>
