<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--UnscheduledStop 1stLd-Writethru a0537 07-24 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Unscheduled Stop, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0537,0163</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jetliner Makes Unscheduled Stop to Check Hydraulics</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS last graf to CORRECT that 111 people declared dead, sted
number of dead and missing.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Continental Airlines jet flying from
Newark, N.J., to the Dominican Republic made an unscheduled stop in
Orlando after the pilot detected a small leak in the hydraulic
system, an airline spokesman said.
   The 133 passengers aboard the Boeing 727 were never in any
danger, and Flight 431 landed safely at Orlando International
Airport shortly before noon Sunday, Continental spokesman Ned
Walker said.
   The unscheduled landing was not declared an emergency, said
airport spokeswoman Carolyn Fennell.
   The system that developed the small leak helps control the wing
flaps and landing gear. Walker said three backup systems were
intact.
   He said the mishap did not resemble the complete hydraulic
system failure that caused a United Airlines DC-10 to crash
Wednesday in Sioux City, Iowa. The crash killed 111 people.
</TEXT>
