family members in the Bronx at the time of the accident. She saved
her baby, Julio Cesar Ordonez, by pushing the boy's carriage with
such force that it went nearly across the street, they said.
   Onlookers managed to lift the 1977 Ford station wagon off Ms.
Ordonez, and a doctor who was nearby tried unsuccessfully to save
Ms. Ordenez.
   The driver, Ventura Lopez, 50, a cleaner for the New York
Transit Authority, was charged with vehicular homicide and driving
while intoxicated, O'Donnell said.
