<FIRST>r a AM-EastStLouis-Phones 1stLd-Writethru a0619 07-24 0318</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-East St Louis-Phones, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0619,0323</SECOND>
<HEAD>City Workers Dialing Long-Distance</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to CORRECT by deleting reference in lead
to dial-a-porn, include that not all `900' calls are to dial-a-porn services.
Pick up 4th graf pvs: `Treasurer Charlotte...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST ST. LOUIS, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A city that has trouble paying for
trash collection has been billed for hundreds of unauthorized
long-distance telephone calls.
   The cash-starved city's monthly bills average $5,000 and include
calls to virtually every state, the Belleville (Ill.) News-Democrat
reported Sunday.
   Many phones in the police and maintenance departments logged
calls to ``900'' prefix lines, the paper said.
   The ``900'' lines are used by dial-a-porn and adult talk
services, as well as by businesses conducting polls or giving out
product and other information. None of the ``900'' numbers on city
bills was in service when called by the paper.
   Treasurer Charlotte Moore said the number of questionable calls
in each month's two-inch-thick bill shows the need for an internal
auditor.
   ``After I suggested it to the (aldermanic) council two years
ago, they cut my staff in half,'' she said. A continuing cash
crunch has made it hard for the city to pay salaries and collect
garbage in recent months.
   In a review of bills from March, April and May, the paper found
hundreds of dollars worth of calls from Texas, Florida and other
places were charged to the city either by reversing the charges or
by using a city credit card number.
   Many outgoing calls from City Hall were equally questionable.
There were calls to a trivia line that gives callers a chance to
win prizes, to the Dunes Hotel in Las Vegas, and to a pay phone in
a St. Louis hospital.
   And there were at least 16 calls from a St. Louis number to the
beeper of a man convicted on Friday on charges of running a cocaine
ring.
</TEXT>
