<HEAD>$Adv06</HEAD>
<HEAD>AGENCIES AND RADIO OUT</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, Aug. 6</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-APN--The Baca</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   
   CRESTONE, Colo. (AP) _ Here is a partial list of spiritual and
environmental projects under way at the Baca:
   _Crestone Mountain Zen Center, 80 acres. Includes a main living
building, organic gardens, wood shop, pottery studio and domed
chapel. Land originally was donated by Hanne and Maurice Strong to
the Lindisfarne Association, along with about 250 other acres, the
sale of which was used to build the buildings.
   _Nada Hermitage Spiritual Life Institute, monastic community of
Carmelite order of Roman Catholics, 80 acres. Includes chapel,
hermitages, kitchen, dining room, library.
   _RedSun Institute, International Educational Center for
Indigenous Peoples, planned 100 acres for a traditional American
Indian village, council lodge and youth camp.
   _Colorado College Southwest Studies program. At the former Aspen
Institute conference center.
   _San Luis Valley Tibetan Project, 200 acres. Proposed community,
monastery, retreat center and medical institute.
   _Haidakhandi Universal Ashram, 46 acres. Temple under
construction. Residential community planned.
   _Sri Aurobindo Learning Center, 61 acres. ``Solar farming
community'' planned.
   _Quinoa Project, 30 acres. Aimed at developing sustainable
high-altitude agricultural system based on Peruvian grain quinoa
and other high-altitude crops.
   _World Unity Garden, Seed Bank, Experimental Gardens.
</TEXT>
