<HEAD>Stock Prices Drop</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices in London surrendered a portion of
their recent gains Monday as the market experienced a technical
correction after its sharp move forward in recent weeks.
   The market opened weaker and retreated steadily during the day.
Dealers said most of the decline was due to market makers cutting
prices in an effort to provoke buying interest. But traders also
reported pockets of profit-taking.
   One trades said the market was ``calming down'' after the the
$21 billion offer by an investor group led by Anglo-French
financier Sir James Goldsmith for BAT Industries PLC July 11.
   The bid energized the London stock market by prompting
speculation of other takeovers.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index ended down
23.9 points, or 1.05 percent, at 2,259.1, just a shade better than
its session low of 2,258.3. The key index began the day with a
3.9-point drop from Friday's close, then declined steadily.
   Volume was 390.4 million shares, compared with 574.1 million
shares Friday.
