Dow Jones industrial average came from trading strategies tied to
the expiration of July stock-related futures and options. With
trading in those contracts concluded, blue chip stocks opened on a
weak note before an afternoon round of futures-related buying
helped them recover some lost ground.
   Among actively traded NYSE-listed issues, Honeywell gained 4{ to
90.
   The company, which had been mentioned lately as a possible
takeover target, today announced a major restructuring program that
includes buying back about 10 million shares of its common stock
and increasing its annual dividend by 25 percent to $2.75 a share.
Honeywell said it is reducing its reliance on the weapons business
and cutting 4,000 jobs.
   McDonalds sank 1~ to 29|. An influential securities analyst was
unimpressed with the fast-food restaurant company's second-quarter
results.
