will be reduced by about $225 million, or 70 cents a share, in the
second quarter by restructuring charges.
   Exxon lost 1, falling to 45} on moderately heavy turnover. The
company today said its second-quarter earnings plunged 87 percent
because of costs associated with the Alaskan oil spill.
   Smithkline Bechman led the actives' list, up [ at 60].
