<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Phone     07-24 0175</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Phone,0184</SECOND>
<HEAD>Earnings, Revenue Up at Bell Atlantic for Second Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bell Atlantic Corp., the regional telephone
holding company, said Monday its profit rose 4.9 percent in the
second quarter on a 6 percent increase in revenue.
   Net income rose to $360.8 million, or $1.84 a share, from $344.1
million, or $1.74 a share, for the same three-month period a year
ago. Revenue rose to $2.88 billion from $2.72 billion.
   Net income for the first half of 1989 rose 5.4 percent to $709.6
million, or $3.61 a share, from $673.2 million, or $3.40 a share, a
year earlier. Revenue was $5.65 billion, a 5.5 percent increase
over the $5.35 billion posted in same period of 1988.
   Growth in business calling was strong, with a 6.4 percent
increase in business access lines in the quarter vs. a year earlier.
   Bell Atlantic is the parent company of New Jersey Bell, Bell of
Pennsylvania, Diamond State Telephone Co. in Delaware and the
Chesapeake and Potomac Telephone Companies serving Maryland,
Virginia, West Virginia and Washington.
</TEXT>
