<FIRST>r f BC-EngineOrders     07-24 0095</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Engine Orders,0099</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thai Airways Orders Eight Pratt &amp; Whitney Engines</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EAST HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Thai airline has ordered eight jet
engines from Pratt &amp; Whitney aircraft in a $65 million deal, the
jet-engine maker said Monday.
   Pratt &amp; Whitney will supply Thai Airways International Ltd. with
eight PW4000 series engines with spare parts, said William Raabe,
vice president for marketing in Pratt's commercial engine division.
   The engines will be used to power three Airbus Industrie
A300-600R aircraft, which will be delivered to the airline in the
fall of 1990, he said.
