<HEAD>ABC Video Units Buys Stake in Grocery Billboard Company</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Capital Cities-ABC Video Enterprises Inc. said
Monday it had acquired a minority interest in In-Store Advertising
Inc., which has developed an electronic billboard system that is in
about 1,000 grocery stores.
   Capital Cities officials declined to disclose how large an
interest they were buying in the privately-held New York-based
concern or how much they had invested.
   In-Store Advertising has developed electronic billboards that
are installed over store aisles and deliver promotional messages
about various products to shopers as they are deciding what brands
to buy.
   Bruce Maggin, executive vice president of the video enterprises
unit, said the investment continues Capital Cities' strategy of
participating ``in a broad spectrum of media activities created by
the new communications technologies.''
   He said it would give his company another vehicle for promoting
its television and cable programming, and said the billboards could
also fit into the marketing strategies of national advertisers who
appear on ABC programs.
