<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Kimberly-Clark     07-24 0122</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Kimberly-Clark,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>Kimberly-Clark Posts Second-Quarter Profit Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Paper products manufacturer Kimberly-Clark Corp.
said Monday its second-quarter profit rose 1.2 percent on increased
sales.
   Profit for the quarter totaled $101.3 million, or $1.26 a share,
compared with a profit of 100.1 million, or $1.25 a share, in the
same quarter of 1988.
   Sales for the second quarter reached nearly $1.4 billion, a 4.1
percent increase over the $1.34 billion in same period last year.
   For the first six months of 1989, net income increased 5.7
percent to $204 million, or $2.54 a share, from $193 million, or
$2.41 a share, in the 1988 period. First-half sales rose 6.9
percent to $2.8 billion from $2.6 billion in the 1988 period.
</TEXT>
